      },
      "schema:name": "Self-Implicative Method",
      "schema:alternateName": [
        "Método Autoimplicativo",
        "Autoimplicative Method"
      ],
      "schema:description": "Authorial methodological concept formulated by Alexandre Mury within A.M.O. and articulated within the Poietic Epistemology of the Image scheme. The Self-Implicative Method designates an artistic method of epistemic intervention through which the artist critically acts upon the contemporary regimes of existence of their own work, recognizing that documentation, cataloguing, circulation, ontologies, metadata, semantic graphs, institutional records, and algorithmic systems actively participate in its historicity, recoverability, and public intelligibility.",
      "schema:creator": {
