      "amo:schemePosition": {
        "@value": "The Self-Implicative Method is a specific authorial methodological concept articulated within the Poietic Epistemology of the Image scheme. The scheme is organizationally superordinate, while the method may operate recursively upon A.M.O. and upon the semantic and documentary infrastructures through which the scheme itself is implemented.",
        "@language": "en"
      },
